==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*mūs'', from Indo-European ''*mūs''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[mus#Old Frisian|mūs]], Old Saxon [[mus#Old Saxon|mūs]] (Dutch [[muis]]), Old High German [[mus#Old High German|mūs]] (German [[Maus]]), Old Norse [[mús]] (Swedish [[mus#Swedish|mus]])

''Indo-European cognates:'' Greek [[μῦς]], Latin [[mus#Latin|mūs]], Armenian [[մուկ]], Old Church Slavonic [[мъшь]] (Russian [[мышь]]), Albanian [[mi|mī]]

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /mu:s/

===Noun===
'''mūs'''
# a [[mouse]]

